deck_excerpt: the deck that never dies ba
Blue-Eyes Chaos Max, Magician of Chaos, Blue-Eyes Chaos Dragon, Blue-Eyes White Dragon, Impcantation, Blue-Eyes Twin Burst Dragon, Black Luster Soldie
deck_description: This deck is focused on ritual summoning Blue-Eyes Chaos Max, Blue Eyes-Chaos Dragon, and Magician of Chaos depending on what your opponent has on their field. Impcantations are what make this deck run so it includes monsters that get cards from the deck and that can get cards from the grave, additionally Chalislime and Preparation of Rites ensure you can work around negates, Impcantation Inception helps in removing Impcantations from your field so you can use your extra deck to possibly summon out a Blue-Twin Burst or a Black Luster Soldier with the help of Scape Goats. Even if Impantations stay on your field you are often left with normal summons to spare so there are several splashed cards to take advantage of this usually ignored benefit. Zaborg is the usual go to for summoning out as many ritual monsters as possible but cards like The Calculator benefit from this deck because you often have one lvl8 dragon plus multiple Impantation monsters which give it massive attack boost to OTK your opponent. Orgoth The Relentless can also be a massive monster that if youre lucky is indestructible and lets you draw cards. Ruins of the Divine Dragon Lords negates monsters effects the turn they are summoned which provides your dragons even more protection and there are cards like Mist Body that provide protection from battle. Because you'll have massive monsters with often attack to spare Twin Swords cuts their attack down slightly so you can attack twice and end even faster. Overall this is a big deck but after weeks of testing it out it is definitely more effective than the 40 card Chaos decks and is a lot more fun. Enjoy.

deck_excerpt: This deck is focused around Red Dragon Archfiend and its many different versions. It has lots of synchro combos to help you summon these monsters as f
deck_description: This deck is built to summon powerful sychro monsters as fast as possible. Some of the main combos include:  -Red Sprinter+Red Resonator -> Red Rising Dragon+Red Resonator -> Red Dragon Archfiend  -Masked Chameleon+Archfiend Cavalry -> Red Dragon Archfiend  -Vice Dragon+Dark/Flare Resonator -> Red Dragon Archfiend  After summoning Red Dragon Archfiend, your best method of summoning your end goal, Red Nova Dragon, is through the use of Chain Resonator.  You can use Resonator Call to make this combo more reliable, and at this point, your Red Nova Dragon should be adequately boosted up with Tuner monsters in the Graveyard from the previous summons. While this is your main goal, the deck contains many other sychros that you can use as stepping stones to the bigger monsters if you need to so you avoid having an open field or risk your combos getting completely shut down.  This deck's main weakness is card effects that can shut down your powerful monsters. This is partially mitigated by Monster Reborn/Call of the Haunted, but if it becomes a problem, adding some protective cards may not be a bad idea.  This deck is a deck that I've been using casually against friends, so it does have some banned cards in it. The side deck has replacement cards if you're using it in a more formal setting. Overall, this probably isn't the most meta deck, but I'm not familiar with all the new summon types at this point because I just recently started playing again, so it's a style that I'm comfortable with. It is not built around the Link ruleset so that is something to keep in mind. Happy dueling, and let me know what you think!

deck_excerpt: A 60-card Lair of Darkness variant. Uses a level 3 engine to Turbo out Rusty Bardiche and Lilith
deck_description: Bardiche Turbo:  Use any two level 3 monsters to summon Cherubini. Send Graff to grave, special summon Scarm. Link into Bardiche. Send PK Ancient Cloak to grave, set either PK Fog Blade or PK Shade Brigandine. Use PK Ancient Cloak's effect to get PK Silent Boots to Hand. Special PK Shade Brigandine and Silent Boots. Get a level 3 of your choice in the end phase from Scarm.     Predaplants:  Use Lonefire Blossoms effect to tribute itself while Lair of Darkess is active to generate 3 tokens in the end phase. This also triggers Darkest Diabolos, as the plants become dark. Search for either Brilliant Fusion, Super Poly (all your opponents monsters are dark, easy targets for Starving Venom Fusion Dragon) or Instant Fusion Sea Monster Theseus for a quick Borreload Savage Dragon with any of your level 3 monsters.     Searching:  Sangan can search out the Predaplants, Lilith, Tour Guide, Destrudo or a Phantom Knight. He acts as a pivot between the different components of the deck. Dragon Shrine and Foolish Burial act as copies of either Destrudo or Darkest Diabolos, as they can summon themselves from the GY. Lilith searches any trap through Trap Trick. Any Trap you want to search for needs to be at two copies. If you draw a copy of Reckless Greed, you can search out the second copy with Lilith for a guaranteed stack to draw 4 cards. Use Edge Imp Sabres to fix your hand when drawing Gem-Knight Lapis (emergency level 3), Mare Mare or Artifact Scythe.     Extra Deck:  The Extra Deck is set up to get you to a Link-4 when using the Destrudo -> Yazi combo. Use the tokens and Mare Mare for either: - Beat Cop, Linkuribok and Mare Mare for the Borrels - 2 tokens to Beat Cop, Beat Cop and Mare Mare to Unicorn. Last token to Linkuriboh, Make Avramax     Side Deck:  I put some other useful searchable traps here

deck_name: Orcust TrainTracks - June 2019 Trinity Format Top 8
deck_excerpt: Lt.Labcoat's 60-card Orcust TrainTracks list - coming Top 8 in the June 2019 Trinity Format monthly cup. Made in collaboration with Ding (the user, no
deck_description:
This Trinity Format deck combines several different Machine archetypes into a singular deck, with a focus on XYZing into Rank 8 or Rank 10.
  • Trains is simple: try and get two Lv10s out, and go into Utopic Dark Infinity.
  • Infinitrack can XYZ into multiple ranks, with the most important one being Dingirsu, the Rank 8.
  • Ancient Gear Box's ability to search Infinitrack Anchor Drill means, if added to hand, you have all the materials for a Dingirsu next turn.
  • Gadgets are Lv4s, which help for getting to a Rank 8, or for playing Gear Gigant. Platinum Gadget is also the go-to Machine Link (Double Headed Anger Knuckle was not released at the time).
  • CyDras can make a Lv10, through Megafleet, and Nachster can resurrect an Infinitrack or Dingirsu.
  • Orcust are... yeah, I think that's pretty clear.
...But, while the combos work great, the overall deck isn't particularly strong. Utopic Dark Infinity is severely hampered by the summon limit, as is Longirsu.

deck_excerpt: Raidraptors are back and ready to ignite the 2019 meta. All cards and strategies explained along with it.
deck_description:
This is a easy deck to play and can beat decks like Salamangreat or Orcust. Please read all your XYZ cards carefully to know what they do, as they are the main engine of the deck. This deck doesn't rely on spells, links(only 2) or Synchro's, your only way to victory is XYZ. (Wise Strix is currently unavailable in TCG format will update soon.) Combo Cards
  1. Raidraptor - Vanishing Lanius - This is your combo starter , you normal summon this and activate its effect to normal summon a Raidraptor card from your hand (Since this deck has 45 cards I've prioritized monsters over hand traps so you can start your combo easy).
  2. Raidraptor - Fuzzy Lanius - Easily my favorite card after ultimate falcon..this card is combo facilitator DON'T SUMMON IT FIRST, normal summon any Raidraptor monster then just activate its effect and summon Fuzzy Lanius, if its sent to the graveyard you can and one Fuzzy Lanius to your hand to start a combo again next turn.
  3. Raidraptor - Mimicry Lanius - This card when sent to the graveyard helps to search any Raidraptor monster or spell card and add it to your hand this is a combo facilitator , you must use this with Raidraptor - Tribute Lanius.
  4. Raidraptor - Tribute Lanius - This is another one of your combo starters , if you draw this card and rest all you have are spells then fear not! you can activate it's effect to send Raidraptor - Mimicry Lanius to the graveyard and use its ability.
  5. Raidraptor - Pain Lanius - This card is also your combo facilitator DON'T SUMMON IT FIRST, normal summon any Raidraptor monster (Level 4 only) and activate Pain Lanius's effect and select that monster to special summon this card to proceed further.
Effect cards
  1. Raidraptor - Booster Strix - This card is a must have in hand , if you're stuck and you need to start a combo then only use it otherwise let it remain in your hand as whenever a Raidraptor monster is about to be destroyed by battle you can banish this card and send the attacking monster to graveyard.
  2. Raidraptor - Necro Vulture - This card can get your Rank-Up-Magic cards from the grave back to your hand by tribitung one Raidraptor monster you control, very useful for huge combo plays.
  3. Raidraptor - Singing Lanius - If you have a XYZ monster you can special summon this card, easy material for another XYZ or link.
  Very important combo (can be game winning at times) Now I talk about one of the MOST important card of the deck... Raidraptor - Last Strix - This card along with Rank-Up-Magic Skip Force is the easiest way to summon your top dogs (or birds) if you have the rank up card in hand you can special summon Last strix , activate its effect and summon Raidraptor - Ultimate Falcon then use your rank up card and summon Raidraptor - Final Fortress Falcon (Its a 200 Atk less version of Chaos Max Dragon) or you can summon Seven Sins whatever you may like.   How to start
  1. If you have ample resources for 3 Raidraptor monsters , then you can go for a Link and a XYZ summon. Summon your 3 monsters by using their effects or by cards like Raidraptor - Nest
  2. Then summon your link monster Raidraptor - Wise Strix and activate its effect to summon any Raidraptor monster from your deck try avoiding combo cards (or you can summon Mimicry lanius and do a XYZ and send it to graveyard to activate its effect)
  3. Now you should have 3 monsters including your link monster.
  4. XYZ summon Raidraptor - Force Strix (in defence) detach one XYZ material and activate its effect to add one Raidraptor card to your hand (if you used Mimicry Lanius as XYZ material , detach it then you can add one more card my using Mimicry's effect).
  5. When your XYZ card effect is resolved your link card will activate its second effect and you can choose a Rank up magic card and set it to your field (I prefer Rank-up-Magic Skip Force) don't use it if you don't have to save it for your top birds , but if you are in an emergency you can.
Rest all is pretty self explanatory read all the spell and trap cards carefully . For any queries , drop a comment and if this works for you consider supporting me on Paypal - A coffee

deck_excerpt: Updated Banish deck for July 2019. Includes the deadliest combos known to all banish dot decks. Let us abuse Trade-in into the ground brethren!
deck_description: The point of this deck is to do three main things:  Cut off your opponent's graveyard  Heal for massive amounts of life points  Feed "Da Eiza"     If you have been playing on ygo pro lately, you have probably seen a variation of this deck. However, my deck has several built in win conditions. This done through a few simple combos. Lets go over a few:  Toll Hike or Extra Toll / Gravekeeper's Servant + Banisher of the Radiance / Macro Cosmos / Dimensional Fissure / Dark Law  This combo does not allow your opponent to even declare an attack. However, Toll hike doesn't allow you to make one either. Therefore, only use that as a last resort. This can stall for a while until you get Gren Maju Da Eiza. You also can use Lava Golem to put your opponent on an 8 turn clock. Lastly, you can use Battle fader (or Gren Maju Da Eiza if you do not have any banished cards; you can perhaps use necroface then have your Gren Maju Da Eiza have zero attack for this) and attack Lava Golem in order to activate Inferno Tempest (I on run one at this time. Even in a 60 card deck, I couldn't find any space for a second one. But two is not bad).  Ledger of the Legerdemain or Seer's Passbook / Inferno Tempest / Eater Of Millions /Storm Castle of Stormberg/ Pot of Desires + Soul Absorption  What makes this combo so op to me is that you're actually benefitting from the cost requirement of these cards. In most decks, the cost of Pot of Desires or even Pot of Indulgence is devestating. However, in this deck it's a huge plus. It allows for you to use the powerful draw engine card Ancient Leaf.  Trade-In + Danger! monsters (With or without banish cards)  Trade-In triggers the effects of Danger! monsters even when they're banished. This is just another bonus in this deck as everything fits well with each other.

deck_description: There are 60 cards in this deck because it is so versatile and it has a lot of draw power. Step 1: Get two monsters on the board to make Knightmare Cerberus and then Knightmare Mermaid. How to get two monsters on the board: - (ROTA>)Neo Space Connector>Neo-Spacian Aqua Dolphin - Two phantom knights monsters - Danger! spam :) - Summon Time Thief Regulator and use his effect. (You wanna have him in the GY later on anyway) Step 2: Use Mermaid effect to send Orcust Knightmare to te GY. Use those two to summon Galatea. Step 3: Banish Orcust Knigtmare and send Harp Horror to the GY. Then banish Horror to special summon Orcust Symbal Skeleton. Send Skeleton and Galatea to the GY and summon The Phantom Knights of Rusty Bardiche. Step 4: Use his effect to send Ancient Cloak to the GY from the deck and set one Fog Blade from the deck. Then you can choose to banish Ancient Cloak to get another Fog Blade or an Silent Boots. Step 5: Banish Skeleton from the GY and summon galatea back from the GY. Use galatea effect and set one Orcustrated Babel. If u drew it then set Orcust Cresendo. Step 6: Overlay Galatea with Dingirsu, The Orcust of the Evening Star. If u went first use 2nd effect, if u went second then use first effect if there is a strong boss monster. From here on you can do a lot and u almost already won if your opponent cannot stop you. If you have a called by the grave in your first hand that would be best case scenario!

deck_excerpt: Go second if possible, then set spells/traps (if you decide to add traps), then Special Summon Mekk-Knights. Link, then Xyz if needed.
deck_description:
I would always go second, since you want to get 2 or more cards in the same column, to di this, set Spell cards first, then summon Mekk-knights - you can get 2 or more cards in the same column to Special Summon Mekk-Knights. I strongly recommend to check out not just mine, but other people's Mekk-Knight decks, also Invoked Mekk-Knights are still great decks to build. The reason I have Yellow Star is to get rid of backrow. Link first, then Xyz. I recommend the following Xyz monsters if you don't have any of the Extra Deck Monsters:
  • Number 38: Hope Harbringer
  • Number 5: Doom Chimera Dragon
  • Number 23: Dark Knight of the Underworld
  • Galaxy-Eyes Photon Lord
  • Galaxy-Eyes Cipher Dragon
Replacement for Link monsters you don't have:
  • Borrelguard
  • Hip Hoshingen
  • Knightmare Phoenix
  • Underclock Taker
NOTE: Feel free to replace anything in this deck with other things you think will work better for you. This is just what I think would be best for this deck.

deck_excerpt: Endymion, Mythical Beasts, Ib the World Chalice Justiciar, Guardragons
deck_description:
Instead of Magicians, this deck uses Draconnet, World Chalice Guardragon and Guardragon Justicia as an extended Guardragon engine. The Guardragon combo:
  • Normal Summon Draconnet
  • Special Summon Guardragon Justicia
  • Synchro Summon Ib the World Chalice Justiciar
  • Ib lets you search for World Legacy Guardragon
  • Use World Legacy Guardragon to return Justicia from the GY to the field
  • Link Ib and Justicia into Beat Cop from the Underworld
  • Ib Special Summons World Chalice Guardragon
  • Link Guardragon into Guardragon Elpy to the right zone Beat Cop points to
  • Use World Legacy Guardragon's effect from the GY to resurrect Justicia
  • Link Justicia and Beat Cop into Triple Burst Dragon into the Extra Monster Zone
  • Use Elpy's effect to Special Summon Destrudo, Darkwurm or Aether
  • Link the summoned Dragon of your choice and Triple Burst Dragon into Guardragon Agarpain
  • Use Agarpains effect to Special Summon Hot Red Dragon Archfiend Abyss (When dealing damage, he resurrects Justicia, Ib or Destrudo from the GY)
  • If you have no more extenders (so far only the Normal Summon was used, Pendulum should still be available), you can Link Agarpain and Elpy into Hieratic Seal of the Heavenly Spheres
You could also incorporate 3 copies of Cynet Mining to further push this aspect of the deck, as it seaches Draconnet.
Building out a deck so I can keep a wishlist of the Altergeist cards I'd like to get.
